# Public display layout (full width)

Venue / TV **display** pages (`apps/display/**`) are shown on large wall screens. **Use the full viewport width.** Edge-to-edge layout is **preferred** over letterboxed or centered “article” columns.

## Page shell

- Root layout: **`w-full`** / **`100dvw`**, **`fixed inset-0`** or **`h-[100dvh]`** — no outer `max-w-*` cap on the page.
- **Avoid** top-level `mx-auto max-w-4xl`, `max-w-7xl`, or similar on the main stage, header band, or primary content column.
- Horizontal padding on the **page edge** should be **minimal** — only what safe-area or a thin visual gutter needs (`px-2`–`px-4` at most). Do not inset the whole UI as if it were a phone card.

## What full width means

| ✅ Preferred | ❌ Avoid on page shells |
|-------------|-------------------------|
| Header bar spans viewport left → right | `max-w-3xl mx-auto` wrapping the whole view |
| Floor mosaic / leaderboard grids fill width | Fixed `80rem` page column with empty side margins |
| Side gutters (rosters, rails) grow into unused space | Centered card floating in unused horizontal space |
| `flex-1 min-w-0` columns sharing a row | Narrow centered column with wide empty gutters |

## Allowed exceptions

- **Sub-regions** inside a full-width page may have intrinsic max width (e.g. a single felt table centered in the spotlight stage, QR tile aspect ratio, pairing card on an otherwise full-bleed background).
- **`max-w-*` on text** for line-length inside a panel is fine; the **panel** should still participate in a full-width layout.
- **`min()` / `clamp()`** that cap *content* size but let the **container** stretch to `100%` is fine.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — whole display view letterboxed
<main className="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-8">...</main>

// ✅ GOOD — page edge-to-edge; inner stage can center its own subject
<div className="fixed inset-0 flex w-full flex-col">
  <header className="w-full shrink-0 px-4">...</header>
  <main className="flex min-h-0 flex-1 w-full">...</main>
</div>
```

## Checklist before merging display layout changes

- [ ] Page root and primary `<main>` use **full viewport width** (no outer `max-w-*`).
- [ ] New side panels / gutters **consume** horizontal space instead of leaving unused margins.
- [ ] Any remaining `max-w-*` is scoped to a **sub-component**, not the display page shell.
